SIMPLE: graze
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Graze
<hw>Graze</hw> <pr>(gr⟦amac⟧z)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>Grazed</conjf> <pr>(gr⟦amac⟧zd)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. &
vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Grazing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE.
<ets>grasen</ets>, AS. <ets>grasian</ets>, fr. <ets>gr⟦ae⟧s</ets> grass.
See <er>Grass</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To feed or supply (cattle,
sheep, etc.) with grass; to furnish pasture for.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A field or two to <qex>graze</qex> his cows.</q>
<rj><qau>Swift.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To feed on; to eat (growing herbage); to eat grass
from (a pasture); to browse.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The lambs with wolves shall <qex>graze</qex> the verdant mead.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To tend (cattle, etc.) while grazing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>When Jacob <qex>grazed</qex> his uncle Laban's sheep.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>To rub or touch lightly the surface of (a thing) in
passing; <as>as, the bullet <ex>grazed</ex> the wall</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Graze</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Graze
<hw>Graze</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To eat grass; to feed
on growing herbage; <as>as, cattle <ex>graze</ex> on the
meadows</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To yield grass for grazing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The ground continueth the wet, whereby it will never
<qex>graze</qex> to purpose.</q> <rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To touch something lightly in passing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Graze</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Graze
<hw>Graze</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of grazing; the
cropping of grass.</def> <mark>[Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Turning him out for a <qex>graze</qex> on the common.</q>
<rj><qau>T. Hughes. </qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A light touch; a slight scratch.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Grazer</ent>⟦br⟧
